As we build using a non-system CLang (due to DD having a dependency on a
version older than we've ever built), it isn't in the hardcoded paths that
rules_go sets in [0].  7.79 moved to using rules_go for the parts of the build
which require CLang, so we need to inject it back into PATH.

The cgo -godefs step that generates the eBPF Go type files also needs clang-12's
resource directory and the kernel headers on the include path (some of the eBPF
C headers, e.g. prebuilt/offset-guess.h, include <linux/sched.h> directly and
pull in a large chunk of the kernel-internal header graph). In our build those
headers are the Debian kernel-headers packages under /usr/src, and the
kernel-internal headers need -D__KERNEL__ plus the kconfig.h/autoconf.h
pre-includes so they don't collide with libc's own definitions (sigset_t,
sigaction, etc.).

Crucially, these flags are injected through a clang wrapper rather than passed
as cgo args after `--`. cgo -godefs records its full argument list in the
"// cgo -godefs -- ..." comment at the top of every generated file, and
DataDog's verify_generated_files diff tests compare that byte-for-byte against
the committed files. Upstream generates them with the kernel headers already on
clang's default search path, so only the deps-derived -I flags appear in the
comment; any extra arg we add there makes every godefs file "out of date" and
fails the build. cgo also does not read CGO_CFLAGS from the environment (only
cmd/go does; cgo itself only special-cases CGO_LDFLAGS, for Bazel back-compat),
so that route does not work either. Wrapping clang keeps the recorded args
identical to upstream while still giving the compiler the flags it needs.

We add -gdwarf-4 to force DWARF version 4 instead of 5. clang-12 emits DWARF 5
by default, which triggers a panic in Go's cgo loadDWARF function ("index out of
range [2] with length 2" in cmd/cgo/gcc.go) on aarch64 when processing certain
kernel struct types in conntrack_types.go.

Verified locally (linux/amd64 and linux/arm64, via Docker) that cgo -godefs
succeeds and the recorded "// cgo -godefs -- ..." comment matches the committed
files for kprobe_types.go, tuple_types.go and conntrack_types.go, against the
actual pinned clang-12 and kernel-headers versions this package fetches.

[0] https://github.com/bazel-contrib/rules_go/blob/9667748a32de210cd4a813b15e9d987103ba0954/go/private/context.bzl#L981

diff --git a/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl b/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl
index 21f462db..5aa1c2e0 100644
--- a/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl
+++ b/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl
@@ -76,13 +76,63 @@
     # TODO(ABLD-410): uses the system clang rather than a hermetic toolchain.
     # On Windows, Go defaults to gcc (MinGW) — no CC override needed, matching
     # the old ninja behavior.
+    cc_setup = ""
     cc_prefix = "CC=clang " if platform == "linux" else ""
+    if platform == "linux":
+        # DataDog generates these godefs files with a non-system clang-12 (they
+        # pin a version older than we ever build with) and rely on the kernel
+        # headers sitting on clang's default search path. In our build the
+        # headers are the Debian kernel-headers packages under /usr/src, clang-12
+        # needs its own resource dir, and the kernel-internal headers pulled in
+        # by e.g. prebuilt/offset-guess.h (<linux/sched.h>) need -D__KERNEL__ plus
+        # the kconfig.h/autoconf.h pre-includes so they don't collide with libc.
+        #
+        # These flags must NOT be passed as cgo args after `--`: cgo -godefs
+        # records its full arg list in the "// cgo -godefs -- ..." comment at the
+        # top of every generated file, and datadog's verify_generated_files diff
+        # tests compare that byte-for-byte against the committed files (generated
+        # upstream with the headers on the default path, so only the deps-derived
+        # -I flags appear). Any extra arg makes every godefs file "out of date"
+        # and fails the build. cgo also ignores CGO_CFLAGS from the environment
+        # (only cmd/go honors it; cgo itself only reads CGO_LDFLAGS, for Bazel
+        # back-compat), so that route is out too. Instead we wrap clang: the extra
+        # flags reach the compiler but never appear in the recorded args, so the
+        # generated files match upstream exactly.
+        #
+        # -gdwarf-4 forces DWARF 4 (clang-12 emits 5 by default) to avoid a panic
+        # in Go's cgo loadDWARF on aarch64 (cmd/cgo/gcc.go "index out of range").
+        kernel_headers_version = "5.10.0-44"
+        karch = {"amd64": "x86", "arm64": "arm64"}[go.sdk.goarch]
+        common_hdr = "/usr/src/linux-headers-{}-common".format(kernel_headers_version)
+        arch_hdr = "/usr/src/linux-headers-{}-{}".format(kernel_headers_version, go.sdk.goarch)
+        kflags = " ".join([
+            "-isystem /opt/clang/lib/clang/12.0.1/include",
+            "-D__KERNEL__",
+            "-include {}/include/linux/kconfig.h".format(common_hdr),
+            "-include {}/include/generated/autoconf.h".format(arch_hdr),
+            "-I {}/arch/{}/include/generated".format(arch_hdr, karch),
+            "-I {}/arch/{}/include/generated/uapi".format(arch_hdr, karch),
+            "-I {}/include/generated/uapi".format(arch_hdr),
+            "-I {}/include".format(arch_hdr),
+            "-I {}/arch/{}/include".format(common_hdr, karch),
+            "-I {}/arch/{}/include/uapi".format(common_hdr, karch),
+            "-I {}/include".format(common_hdr),
+            "-I {}/include/uapi".format(common_hdr),
+            "-gdwarf-4",
+        ])
+        cc_setup = (
+            "CGODEFS_CC=$(mktemp) && " +
+            "printf '#!/bin/sh\\nexec clang \"$@\" {kflags}\\n' > \"$CGODEFS_CC\" && " +
+            "chmod +x \"$CGODEFS_CC\" && "
+        ).format(kflags = kflags)
+        cc_prefix = "CC=\"$CGODEFS_CC\" "
 
     cmd = (
-        "set -euo pipefail && ROOT=$PWD && cd {src_dir} && " +
+        "set -euo pipefail && ROOT=$PWD && {cc_setup}cd {src_dir} && " +
         "GOROOT=$ROOT/{goroot} {cc_prefix}$ROOT/{go} tool cgo -godefs -- {includes} -fsigned-char {src_file} | " +
         "$ROOT/{genpost} {genpost_args} > $ROOT/{out}"
     ).format(
+        cc_setup = cc_setup,
         cc_prefix = cc_prefix,
         goroot = go.sdk.root_file.dirname,
         src_dir = src.dirname,
@@ -95,6 +145,9 @@
     )
 
     env = dict(go.env)
+    # PATH is no longer inherited from the environment, so we need to extend it
+    # here so the CC wrapper's bare `clang` resolves to /opt/clang.
+    env["PATH"] = ":".join(["/opt/clang/bin", env["PATH"]])
     env["CGO_ENABLED"] = "1"
 
     # run_shell needed: genpost reads stdin and writes stdout, so the pipeline
